Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State will, on Thursday, June 6, inaugurate the state’s sixth Assembly in Ado-Ekiti. The Clerk of the House, Mr. Tola Esan, confirmed  on Saturday in Ado Ekiti that Fayemi had issued a proclamation to that effect. The event is scheduled for the main chamber of the Assembly at 10 a. m. Esan urged members of the State Executive Council, religious and traditional rulers as well as the general public to be part of the occasion. The All Progressives Congress (APC) won all the 26 seats in the assembly. 